President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Geoffrey William Seiji Okamoto of California to be Deputy Under Secretary of the Treasury for International Finance. Upon confirmation, Okamoto will be designated as an Assistant Secretary of the Treasury for International Finance. Okamoto currently serves as Deputy Assistant Secretary for International Finance at the Treasury Department. He has previously held positions as Majority Staff Director for the Senate Banking Subcommittee on Financial Institutions and Consumer Protection, as well as Policy Director for the House Financial Services Subcommittee on Monetary Policy and Trade. Okamoto began his career as a consultant at KPMG. He holds a B.S. from California State Polytechnic University, Pomona, and an M.P.P. from Georgetown University. President Trump has also announced his intent to appoint individuals to be Members of the Board of Governors of the United Service Organizations Inc. for three-year terms, but the specific names have not been mentioned in the article.